column5: Anybody know how many teams are in?
Not sure on this weekends tourney - all I know is I couldn't get a room at Papertown 10 days ago - they are booked. I've heard around 50 for next weeks tournament. I'll be there for that one.
Sounds like the local economy has had a toll on the local anglers so there are only 45-46 entries so far. Any idea how the bait situation is looking? Sounds like salties are tough to come by.Ryan

Ryan if dropping through Fargo is a doable plan for you, I have large salted and frozen Fatheads on hand at Gander Mtn already prepacked in tubs, they work well too. I also have preserved Rainbow Shiners in large packages. Both are "Border Friendly".
According to the weather network looks like killer weather up there 54 to 65 K winds Snowfall warnings and squalls up to 30 cm of snow Anybody heard if day one was cancelled or a go?
Eddy,We are heading up through Fargo. Send me a PM with your info and I will call you.Thanks, Ryan
We plan on coming through Fargo on Wednesday (10/14/09) around 8 pm. We would like to pick up some bait what are the hours at Gander Mountain?

Gander is opens at 9:00 AM and closes at 9:00 PM. Sundays open noon tell 6 PM.The Golden Coral is right next door, good chow, if you pull in before 9 you can grab a breakfeast buffet and pop in after 9 if that works with your schedule.I will be there before 9.
